<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{the drunk. he blinks slowly, tongue lolling outside his mouth. he watches woodward approach.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{woodward coming still closer.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{the drunk. he blinks very slowly now. maybe he isn't even certain woodward's there.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{woodward stopping in front of the drunk. they look at each other for a long time. then:}
<C>__{woodward}
<D>__{who are you?}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{the drunk. nothing, no reaction.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{woodward studying the other man.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{the drunk. and he blinks again, then slowly, shivering, begins sliding down the wall. woodward reaches for him, holds him up.}
<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{woodward managing to get out his wallet, take out some bills. he starts up the ramp with the drunk, and as they disappear up the ramp out of sight, he gives the drunk the money.}
<C>__{woodward}
<D>__{here.}
<P>__{(softly)}
<D>__{forget your troubles and just be happy.}
